1. It is important to remember that every individual is unique and should be treated as such, regardless of their nationality or immigration status.2. Deportation is a serious matter and should not be used as a blanket solution for every situation.3. Building a wall may not be an effective solution to the issue of illegal immigration, as there are other ways for people to enter a country.4. It is crucial to address the root causes of why people are leaving their home countries and coming to the US in the first place, such as poverty, violence, and political instability.5. Instead of focusing solely on deportation and building a wall, efforts should be made to find a more comprehensive and humane solution to the problem of illegal immigration.6. It is essential to remember that the vast majority of undocumented immigrants are law-abiding citizens who contribute positively to society.7. It is also important to note that the US has a long history of accepting and integrating immigrants, and this tradition should be continued in a fair and just manner.8. Ultimately, the issue of immigration is complex and requires a thoughtful and nuanced approach that takes into account the needs and rights of all parties involved.
